People said that Hannover is a city of horses. Michaela said that Hannover is a city of horse shit. She didn't particularly say that Hannover is a shitty town. What she meant was the feces left behind, scattered all over the city after some public demonstration that got the police riding out on the horses back. .
"I don't know, i mean, ever since i was small, it was the stinking smell that i noticed more, not the pretty big horses that every little kid supposedly fall in love to," she said. .
That moment Fionn honestly just thought that Michaela said those words to seem edgy and different.
Waktu itu ngk pake makeup soalnya.

The story about the shoes happened years before the cancer. Sometimes in the middle of chemo Fionn would think about the battered two shoes, hanging still above the road on a thin electric wire that ran across a small road at the outskirts of town. Thing was, if they had to point out where that road was once again, they had to ride the train all the way to the end of the 2nd line, walked thirty minutes passed an empty field, turning right into a forest and off the track, spend another forty-five walking in circle underneath the pine leaves, before appearing near a small collection of houses two hours walk-away from the nearest train station. In short, they couldn't remember how to get there for the second time, all thanks to Hoang's idea of a google map-free adventure.
.
It was a really hot day in August (though Hoang said that it was nothing for his 'superior vietnamese skin'). Both the girls were already battered and they decided to sit for a while on the steps of a seemingly-abandoned house, lounging near the road with face flushed from the heat and shirts drenched in sweat. Fionn's feet were aching then and he took off his shoes, trying to get some air (more like polluting the air, according to Michaela).
.
"Hey, it's not that bad. Stinking feet is, after all, a genetic condition everyone wearing a shoe on a hot summer day will inherit," Fionn protested.
.
"Well, your feet aren't stinking, Fionn. More like decaying. God, i bet even a corpse wouldn't smell this bad," Michaela said.
.
"Oh please, Mike," Fionn scoffed. "Your feet could be even worse than mine."
.
Michaela argued back that hers would certainly not, until the conversation turned into some sort of a feet-smelling challenge. The topic got even sidetracked, but the most important scene of the day, was how it ended with Hoang stealing both of Fionn's shoes, tied the strings together, throwing it back and forth with Enes, before it ended up accidentally on the electric wire. Fionn walked barefooted for the rest of that scorching day, accompanied by either the group's laughter or apology for the rather unfortunate event.

There's a house at the end of the road.
It stood still, it stood alone.
Every time little Pete took a walk on a misty little morn,
It's a wail that he heard, a bone-chilling desperate moan.
And when he turns his head, frightened and still curiously sought,
it's a figure of a woman peeking from the top window,
with eyes crimson and bloody as a rose.
"But papa it's just a tale too old, 
A bedtime story to scare the folk."
Old man Peter just shook his head and spoke.
"It is not a nightmare but for little Jon, 
Who walk down the road one chilling winter morn,
Gone he was for three hours or four,
Till a neighbor found him walking aimlessly down the road
Crying and confused he had his hand raised at his front, 
Clawing at what he lost, the socket that were his eyes left hollow."

............................................................
1. Tanus, Stephanie, Hanie, ÊúàÈúì (yue ni), Chen, Colonel. I got lots of nicknames.
2. Think in English, speak in Indonesia, whisper in German.
3. Only child but i got a cute lil bro who barks named Carlos von Rais (no kidding).
4. I'm a writer and won't stop doing it till the rest of my life. Well, i hope so.
5. Linkin Park's a huge influence. MCR, Foo Fighters, 30STM and Greenday come up next. 
6. James Blake and XXYYXX is a different genre so they get a new number.
7. So does K Hip Hop. Watching Beenzino's live is a new dream of mine. 
8. Can do Eminem's Love The Way You Lie and Macklemore's Thrift Shop and so damn proud about it (don't know why).
9. Can do Gamelan Jawa. Nyinden and Bonang. Loving it. 
10. Going to germany next year or so i hope. LMU - M√ºnchen, International Relation.
11. Have learned Mandarin, French and Italian (suck at those three) Currently learning German (still suck). 12. Like to wear rings and snapbacks (and sometimes beats around my neck)
13. Fell in love with Italy without having to go there. So it's just decent that i want to go there someday.
14. I want to marry a foreigner. My mom said that my future husband has to look like James Bond. HAHA.
15. Ah, i forgot about Hans Zimmer and Chopin.
16. Talking about Chopin, Nocturne in C# Minor is my favorite. My piano skill sucks though (don't even start with violin)
17. Fell in love with History. WWII in particular 
18. Saving Private Ryan and Band of Brothers change my life, i suppose.
